<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="713" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">McCormick</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-15"><hi rend="italic">February 15,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay transmits to Mr. McCormick the reply of the Japanese Government
                            to the proposal of the United States relating to the neutrality of
                            China.)</p>
                        <p>(<hi rend="smallcaps">Note.</hi>—See inclosure 2 to dispatch No. 45,
                            February 15, 1904, from Japan, printed on <ref target="#pg_420">page
                                420</ref>.)</p>
                    </div>
